addSongId(uint256,string).details: Only owner function to add a song ID to the contract.

params.songTokenURI: the token URI of the song

assignTokenIdToSongId(uint256,uint256).details: Only owner function to assign a tokenId to a song ID

params.songId: the song ID to tie to the token ID
params.tokenId: the ID of the token to assign a song ID to

claimSongRoyaltyRewards().details: Function for NFT holders to claim their song royalty rewards.

createToken(string).details: Only owner function to mint a new NFT.

params.newTokenURI: the token URI on IPFS for the NFT metadata

returns._0: the ID of the newly minted NFT

createTokenAfterTrackPackBurn(address).details: Function for track pack contract to mint NFT after track pack burn

params.receiver: the receiver of the new NFT

returns._0: the ID of the newly minted NFT

depositRewardsForSong(uint256).details: Function to deposit rewards for a single song.

params.songId: the ID of the song the deposit is for

depositRewardsForSongInChunks(uint256,ui.details: Function to deposit rewards for a single song in chunks to avoid running out of gas.

params.endIndex: the last index to deposit rewards for with this chunk
params.songId: the ID of the song the deposit is for
params.startIndex: the first index to deposit rewards for with this chunk

getRoleAdmin(bytes32).details: Returns the admin role that controls `role`. See {grantRole} and {revokeRole}. To change a role's admin, use {_setRoleAdmin}.

getUserSongIDs(address).details: Function to get all song IDs for tokens that a given user owns.

params.userAddress: the user's address to get song IDs of

returns._0: list of song IDs for a user's NFTs

getUserTokenIDs(address).details: Function to get all token IDs for tokens that a given user owns.

params.userAddress: the user's address to get token IDs of

returns._0: list of token IDs for a user's NFTs

getUserTokenURIs(address).details: Function to get all token URIs for tokens that a given user owns.

params.userAddress: the user's address to get token URIs of

returns._0: list of token URIs for a user's NFTs

grantRole(bytes32,address).details: Grants `role` to `account`. If `account` had not been already granted `role`, emits a {RoleGranted} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

removeSongIdByIndex(uint256).details: Only owner function to remove a song ID from the contract.

params.songIdIndex: the index into the song ID array for the song ID to remove

removeTokenIdFromSongIdByIndex(uint256,u.details: Only owner function to remove a token ID from a song ID.

params.songId: the song ID that the token ID is being removed from
params.tokenIdIndex: the index of the token ID that is being removed from the song ID

renounceRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from the calling account. Roles are often managed via {grantRole} and {revokeRole}: this function's purpose is to provide a mechanism for accounts to lose their privileges if they are compromised (such as when a trusted device is misplaced). If the calling account had been revoked `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must be `account`.

revokeRole(bytes32,address).details: Revokes `role` from `account`. If `account` had been granted `role`, emits a {RoleRevoked} event. Requirements: - the caller must have ``role``'s admin role.

setTokenURI(uint256,string).details: Setter function for the token URI of an NFT.

params.newTokenURI: the token URI to update the NFT with
params.tokenId: the ID of the NFT to update the token URI of

updateSongTokenURI(uint256,string).details: Only owner function to update the token URI for a song

params.songId: the song ID to update the token URI of

updateUnassignedTokenURI(string).details: Only owner function to update the token URI given to songs NFTs before they are assigned a song
